design:
Schema:
- Envelope: { topic:"issues", action:"added"|"updated"|"removed", revision:number, snapshot?:boolean, payload:object, meta:{ sent_at:string } }
- Payload:
  - added: { issues: Issue[] }
  - updated: { issues: Issue[] }
  - removed: { ids: string[] }
Handshake:
- Client -> Server: { subscribe:"issues", accepts:["push-v2","push-v1"] }
- Server -> Client: { subscribed:"issues", protocol:"push-v2" }
- On subscribe, server immediately sends `added` snapshot with all issues.
Ordering & batching:
- `revision` increments per subscription; messages may be batched; client ignores stale revisions.
Compatibility:
- If server replies with `push-v1`, client stays on legacy fetch-on-notify path.
